# Docs Sync Rules — Hermes Fleet

## Canonical vs mirror

| Type | Write here | Sync command |
|------|------------|--------------|
| Tool reviews, TOOLS-*, design refs, tool chest | `_core-scripts/shared-profile-content/docs/` | `npm run sync:docs -- -Write` |
| Profile constitution, session state | `<profile>/TRUTH.md`, `ReCall.md` | Manual |
| Skills, doctor scripts, review rules | `shared-profile-content/skills|scripts|rules|prompts/` | `npm run fleet:sync` (hub) |

**JonBeatz** is often where Jon works — **not** where tool knowledge should live exclusively. See `FLEET-TOOLS-KNOWLEDGE.md`.

## Path standards

- **START-HERE.md** is the primary entry point per profile
- Use relative links in profile docs — avoid hardcoding sibling repo paths unless hub-specific (COMMAND-CENTER)
- Profile root varies (`JonBeatz`, `DigitalStudioz`, etc.) — never MSC deploy paths unless Jon opened MSC repo

## Version tracking

- Sync version across **profile** `package.json`, `TRUTH.md`, `MASTER-COMMANDS.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`
- **Shared skeleton** has its own `VERSION.md` — bump when fleet artifacts ship
- Use **`npm run version:sync`** (Python UTF-8) for README badges
- Run **`npm run encoding:check`** before doc commits

## Issue management

- Profile bugs → `.cursor/docs/ISSUES-RESOLVED.md` or `npm run log:fix`
- Fleet-wide tool gotchas → `TOOLS-REFERENCE.md` Risks section + optional vault atomic note

## Commit discipline

- Doc-only: `docs:` prefix when Jon requests commit
- Tool review sessions: prefer **`_core-scripts` + hub** commits together
- Do **not** auto-commit unless Jon asks

## MCP + skills

- Project MCP secrets in `.env.local` — `npm run sync:mcp-env`
- IN USE skills → vendored under `shared-profile-content/skills/` when possible
- UI skills read order: Hallmark → NovaMira-Design → MSC-UI-Taste → Premium-UI → Emil motion pack
